{"TopicId":188738,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"Breaking 2000 m/s at sea level.","CreatedByName":"xoonZG","CreatedById":77545,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T00:00:20Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"xoonZG","CreatedById":77545,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T00:00:20Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3498db;\u0022\u003EHey folks,\u003Cbr\u003E\nMe and my friend had a crazy challenge to go as fast as possible below 1000m.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3498db;\u0022\u003EWe managed 1984 m/s.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022image0.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002275.00\u0022 height=\u0022768\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://cdn.discordapp.com/attachments/273176192138346496/630916752175530003/image0.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3498db;\u0022\u003E(Yes, this is a poor image. )\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3498db;\u0022\u003EThe issue we faced is everything overheating and exploding around 1800 m/s, which seems to be a almost hard limit without shenanigans.\u00A0\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3498db;\u0022\u003EDoes anyone know if this is possible without cheating?\u00A0\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geonovast","CreatedById":179753,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T00:15:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMoving to Gameplay Questions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood luck with this challenge. \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Guest","CreatedById":-1,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T05:58:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat is insane. If you ever break 2000 m/s somebody needs to design you a badge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis us a great idea for a challenge too, except that your result is so good it would likely discourage most of us from even trying.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Redacted","CreatedById":194844,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T07:26:21Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe trick to breaking 2000ms is the run with a heat-shield instead of a nose-cone. The rest of the craft, wether it\u00A0be it a rocket or \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E of some sort, needs to be only as wide as the heat-shield. This way\u00A0the brunt on the aero forces are concentrated at one point, rather then across the body / wings.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSide note: I have a rather unorthodox \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Single Stage to Orbit\u0022\u003ESSTO\u003C/abbr\u003E on KerbalX that can break 4000ms while transitioning to orbit. Its named \u201CRedshift\u201D and uses a combination of ACS thrusters and Scramjet (above 1250 ms). It can easily launch itself from Kerbin\u2019s \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Sphere of Influence\u0022\u003ESoI\u003C/abbr\u003E using 200-300 liquid fuel.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHHans","CreatedById":197939,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T09:01:32Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223683422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188738\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221570514280\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022167629\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Brikoleur\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Brikoleur said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis us a great idea for a challenge too, except that your result is so good it would likely discourage most of us from even trying.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell... I did try... But only managed 1800-something m/s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy last try had an interesting failure mode: once the leading fairing exploded due to overheating, everything else went in an instant due to excessive g-forces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are going fast enough even air becomes as soft as a brick wall! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S. How about moving this to the challenges subforum?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-10-08T09:04:12Z\u0022 title=\u002210/08/2019 09:04  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EOctober 8, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by AHHans\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T11:58:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 data-embed-src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/itr6vGHEYRE?feature=oembed\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t think any has beaten this.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Duck McFuddle","CreatedById":188882,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T12:00:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried a similar thing, only my problem was not having a long enough space to drive down. I would have to transport my craft down to one of Kerbin\u0027s poles and that seems like a lot of work.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"xoonZG","CreatedById":77545,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-10-08T13:03:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223683463\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022188738\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221570525292\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022197939\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHHans\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, AHHans said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell... I did try... But only managed 1800-something m/s.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMy last try had an interesting failure mode: once the leading fairing exploded due to overheating, everything else went in an instant due to excessive g-forces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you are going fast enough even air becomes as soft as a brick wall! \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S. How about moving this to the challenges subforum?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:#3498db;\u0022\u003EI created a challenge thread, feel free to participate:\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u002277545\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1814048513\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/188748-the-hot-needle-challenge-go-as-fast-as-possible-below-600m/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:209px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}